a
screening
tool
to
detect
psychosocial
adjustment
of
children
with
cystic
fibrosis
a
tool
to
assess
psychosocial
adjustment
of
school
age
children
with
cystic
fibrosis
was
developed
using
three
instruments
a
standardized
open
ended
parent
interview
a
self
administered
teacher
questionnaire
and
a
self
administered
parent
demographic
data
form
the
three
instruments
enabled
the
pediatric
nurse
practitioner
to
make
a
clinical
assessment
of
the
child
s
psychosocial
adjustment
this
assessment
was
then
checked
for
validity
by
means
of
a
social
worker
interview
implications
for
further
research
are
discussed
